Last night was great. Most people know that during the pandemic my wife @maria_knipt was diagnosed with breast cancer the same week we found out she was pregnant with our second. She had a mastectomy and went through chemotherapy while pregnant through the pandemic. Our love for traveling and food led us to watch #somebodyfeedphil @phil.rosenthal and not only is it an entertaining show it brought happiness, laughter, smiles and positivity to a dark time. Meeting him last night and sharing our story in front of a crowd was something I looked forward to for months. I felt it was important to let him know in person what an impact he made for us. He was just as incredible and caring in person as he is on the show. Thank you again @phil.rosenthal

Im just sitting in the waiting room again at the hospital waiting for my wife’s @maria_knipt 2 out of 3 reconstruction surgeries to be complete. Going to be reaching 3 years soon of her battle with breast cancer and I was just thinking of how thankful I am to everyone who has helped us along the way. I’m very thankful to @xderskix for making us get help when I didn’t want it or ask for it. My wife along with all women who fight this battle are true warriors and I wish I could be half as strong. Thank you to everyone again for continued support for my family. I’ll forever be grateful! #fuckcancer #breastcancer

Today is a sad day for @madetolasttattoo . Today was the last day for @slootattoos to work at the shop and moving forward to working at his new shop @rubytigertattoo . All I can say is a I took a gamble against what everyone said to me in hiring him almost 7 yrs ago. Everyone said his style didn’t fit with the @madetolasttattoo look. The only look we have is doing good versatile tattoos and treating people with respect. Jeremy meets all of those requirements and has shown not only love and respect to his clients but he has shown all of his coworkers the same. He’s opening his new shop with 3 other great tattooers and they’re very lucky to have him in their lives. You will truly be missed!
Thank you @candyaliens for being so tough and knocking it out. @madetolasttattoo #madetolasttattoo

Thank you to everyone! All of my clients, friends, coworkers, family and everyone who has continued to support me and my career all of these years. 2022 was a great one! 2023 will mark 26 years of tattooing for me. Every year I get to spend living my life as a tattooer, father, husband and traveler is a great one. I strive to make every year better so let’s get going 2023! I hope to see everyone at @madetolasttattoo in the many years to come.

One of the most important people involved in my tattoo career came by and paid me a visit today at @madetolasttattoo Without @rodneyraines I wouldn’t be where I am today. He put North Carolina on the map for tattooing many years ago and gave most of us the knowledge of a true hard working tattooer that gives it his all. After 7 years of @madetolasttattoo being open this visit made it all worth it. You mean the world to me my friend and thank you for everything! If you aren’t following @rodneyraines you’re missing out on one of the best.

When I received the invite to the 40yr anniversary party for @royaltattoodk it was one of those moments where I looked around and said, who me? I’ve always looked up to @henning_royaltattoo as being a leader in the tattoo community and one of the most humble humans I’ve ever met. From the moment he met me he always made it a point to spend time having a quality conversation with me and seeing how life is going. It was a huge honor to be amongst incredible people and talent to say the least this weekend. Thank you to everyone involved for making such a great anniversary party and welcoming my whole family with open arms.

Regardless of whatever ups and downs 2023 may have had it was a great one. As long as my family is healthy and @madetolasttattoo is thriving I’m happy. I can never thank my clients and all of the clients of @madetolasttattoo enough. I’m blown away more and more every year of the growth of our shop and the continued support all around the world. Posted @withregram • @timhendricks PLEASE READ - @texasbydeath_true and I set up a gofundme to help our friend @timbecktattoos through this difficult time.
Tim was diagnosed with stage 4 colon cancer in 2022 and after 3 major surgeries and 12 rounds of chemotherapy it stopped the cancer briefly,
but now it’s come back, in his liver and lungs.
We’re trying to raise money for him to fight this without having the stress of financial hardships in taking care of his family.
And I gotta say, if Tim would’ve said no to this gofundme, Aaron and I would’ve set it up anyhow and risked him being angry at us.
We love you @timbecktattoos, and we’re here for you.
Please donate and reshare. And if you can’t donate then share it, it only takes a second or two and I can’t express how much it would mean to me. 
Please help me help my friend Tim. The link is in my bio
